            </tr>
            <tr><td>1</td><td>57.2987</td></tr>
            <tr><td>0.5</td><td>57.2965</td></tr>
            <tr><td>0.1</td><td>57.2958</td></tr>
            <tr><td>0.01</td><td>57.2958</td></tr>
            <tr><td>0.001</td><td>57.2958</td></tr>
        </table><br>

        <p>Result: The limit of f(x) = x / sin(x) as x → 0 is approximately 57.2957 because both sides approach the same value.</p>
        </Accordion>

        <Accordion
        title="Example 4: (Click to View)"
        id="Example 4: (Click to View)d"
        direction="left"
        justifycontent="flex-start"
        fontsize1="2rem"
        fontsize2="1.5rem"
        >
        <h3>Problem 4: lim<sub>x → π/2</sub> cos x</h3>
        <p>Solution: Using a table of values to estimate the limit from both sides.</p>

        <p>Left-hand approach (x → π/2⁻):</p>
        <table border="1" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0">
            <tr>
                <th>x</th>
                <th>f(x)</th>
            </tr>
            <tr><td>1.5</td><td>-0.9991</td></tr>
            <tr><td>1.57</td><td>-1</td></tr>
            <tr><td>1.570</td><td>-1</td></tr>
